{
  "texts": [
    "Several studies have demonstrated that LLM based models obtain far better accuracy scores when compared to more traditional ML based Sentiment Analysis models for a wide range of applications.",
    "Furthermore, LLM based models are capable of tackling more nuanced problem statements.",
    "(44) (45) Ranging from the prediction of stock prices based on twitter sentiment (46) to accurately predicting the sentiment of a given news headline (47), studies have shown that LLMs have performed exceedingly well in all these areas.",
    "Other NLP MethodsThere exists a rich array of established and recent NLP methods.",
    "These include Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA), word and phrase frequency and N-Gram analyses, word and phrase distances, text summarization (abstractive, extractive and hybrid), topic identification, Named Entity Recognition (NER), syntactic and semantics analyses and aspect mining among others, including framed methods such as public sentiment scenario analyses (37)."
  ]
}